    <section class="awareness">
        <h1>Emergency Awareness</h1>
        <p>Learn how to handle emergency situations effectively with our simple and practical tips.</p>
        <div class="tips">
            <div class="tip">
                <img src="https://png.pngtree.com/png-clipart/20230814/original/pngtree-health-card-with-boy-having-head-injury-health-head-injury-pupil-vector-picture-image_10633845.png" alt="Head Injury">
                <h2>Head Injuries</h2>
                <p>Steps to handle head injury safely.</p>
                <button class="open-modal" data-title="Head Injuries" data-content="Keep the injured person still and avoid unnecessary movement. Look for signs of concussion, like confusion, dizziness, or memory loss. Apply a cold pack to reduce swelling, but avoid direct pressure on any open wound. Seek medical attention immediately if symptoms worsen.">Learn More</button>
            </div>

            <div class="tip">
                <img src="https://media.istockphoto.com/id/613327526/vector/burns.jpg?s=612x612&w=0&k=20&c=njkdb2h2zRkRoREVGrVtqyqGfeNgzRjtHnjgyXKb2DY=" alt="Burns">
                <h2>Burns</h2>
                <p>Tips for handling minor and severe burns.</p>
                <button class="open-modal" data-title="Burns" data-content="For minor burns, cool the area under running water for 10-15 minutes. Avoid using ice directly. Do not pop any blisters that form. For severe burns, call emergency services immediately and keep the burn covered with a clean, non-stick cloth.">Learn More</button>
            </div>

            <div class="tip">
                <img src="https://www.shutterstock.com/image-vector/set-sad-character-man-injuries-600nw-1368823949.jpg" alt="Fractures">
                <h2>Fractures</h2>
                <p>Steps to handle fractures safely.</p>
                <button class="open-modal" data-title="Fractures" data-content="Stabilize the injured area with a splint or padding. Avoid moving the injured limb unnecessarily. Elevate the limb slightly if possible to reduce swelling, and seek professional medical help immediately.">Learn More</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

